# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Gemini API Configuration
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Get your API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
#
# IMPORTANT SECURITY MEASURES:
# 1. Restrict the API key in Google Cloud Console:
#    - Add application restrictions (HTTP referrers or IP addresses)
#    - Limit API access to "Generative Language API" only
# 2. Never commit this file with actual keys
# 3. Rotate keys regularly (monthly recommended)
# 4. Monitor usage for unauthorized requests
#
# Format: Should start with "AIza" and be exactly 39 characters
# Example: AIzaSyXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
GEMINI_API_KEY="YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY_HERE"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Next.js Configuration (Automatic - DO NOT SET MANUALLY)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are set automatically by Next.js and your deployment platform
# NODE_ENV="development" | "production" | "test"
# VERCEL_ENV="development" | "preview" | "production"
# VERCEL_URL="your-app.vercel.app"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: Additional Configuration
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Add other environment variables as needed for your deployment

# Custom API URL (if different from default)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL="https://api.your-domain.com"

# Analytics (if using)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID="G-XXXXXXXXXX"

# Error Tracking (if using Sentry)
# SENTRY_DSN="https://xxx@xxx.ingest.sentry.io/xxx"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN="https://xxx@xxx.ingest.sentry.io/xxx"

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Development vs Production
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Development (.env.local):
#   - Uses localhost
#   - Less restrictive CORS
#   - Verbose logging enabled
#   - Hot reload enabled
#
# Production (Deployment Platform Environment Variables):
#   - MUST set GEMINI_API_KEY in platform settings
#   - DO NOT use .env files in production
#   - Use platform's secret management:
#     * Vercel: Project Settings â†’ Environment Variables
#     * AWS: Secrets Manager or Parameter Store
#     * Azure: Key Vault
#     * GCP: Secret Manager
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY CHECKLIST
# ============================================================================
#
# Before deploying to production:
# [ ] New Gemini API key generated (not the one from .env.local)
# [ ] API key restricted in Google Cloud Console
# [ ] .env.local NOT committed to git
# [ ] Environment variables set in deployment platform
# [ ] API key rotated within last 30 days
# [ ] Monitoring set up for API usage
# [ ] Rate limiting tested and working
# [ ] Security headers verified
